school is terrible about tardiness.

74
00:05:44,834 --> 00:05:46,586
-Oh. At Otter Bay?
-Yes.

75
00:05:47,212 --> 00:05:49,755
That's where we're going.
My son, Ziggy, is about to start.

76
00:05:49,839 --> 00:05:52,217
-Ziggy, like Ziggy Stardust?
-Yeah.

77
00:05:52,342 --> 00:05:53,801
-That's a great name.
-Thanks.

78
00:05:53,885 --> 00:05:55,469
This is my daughter, Chloe.

79
00:05:55,553 --> 00:05:58,348
The one shrinking from
embarrassment over there.

80
00:05:59,015 --> 00:06:00,266
Are you new to Monterey?

81
00:06:00,558 --> 00:06:02,608
Yeah, we just moved here a few weeks ago.

82
00:06:03,437 --> 00:06:05,237
Well, I'm Madeline Martha Mackenzie.

83
00:06:05,731 --> 00:06:07,524
I always say the Martha,
but no one calls me that.

84
00:06:07,608 --> 00:06:09,026
They call me Madeline.

85
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:11,237
I'm Jane, Jane no-middle-name Chapman.

86
00:06:11,862 --> 00:06:15,366
Jane no-middle-name
Chapman, I like you already.

87
00:06:15,741 --> 00:06:19,036
You're an intrinsically nice person, and
I have a nose for these sorts of things.

88
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:22,790
No. What Madeline had was a
nose for everybody else's business.

89
00:06:22,915 --> 00:06:24,041
Oh, my God.

90
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:25,251
Believe me, I know.

91
00:06:27,712 --> 00:06:28,754
Um…

92
00:06:28,963 --> 00:06:30,756
Do you need a ride or something?

93
00:06:31,090 --> 00:06:32,382
I'm a stay-at-home mom myself,

94
00:06:32,466 --> 00:06:35,345
so I'm happy to welcome
another full-time mom to the ranks.

95
00:06:35,429 --> 00:06:37,805
You know, sometimes I
think it's like us against them,

96
00:06:37,889 --> 00:06:39,433
the career mommies.

97
00:06:39,558 --> 00:06:42,894
Them and all their various board
meetings that are so important.

98
00:06:42,978 --> 00:06:45,063
Google this, Yahoo that.

99
00:06:45,647 --> 00:06:47,732
Please, I think they spend more
time on those board meetings

100
00:06:47,816 --> 00:06:50,026
than they do actually parenting,
if you know what I mean.

101
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:51,987
My mom's an active talker.

102
00:06:52,821 --> 00:06:54,072
I actually have a part-time job.

103
00:06:54,156 --> 00:06:56,742
Yeah, so do I, but it
doesn't really count.

104
00:06:57,159 --> 00:06:59,828
The over and under in
this town is about $150,000.

105
00:06:59,953 --> 00:07:04,750
I work in community theater, 20 hours
a week, so I'm definitely an "under."

106
00:07:05,292 --> 00:07:07,086
-What do you do?
-Just bookkeeping.

107
00:07:07,170 --> 00:07:09,589
So most definitely an "under," too.

108
00:07:11,007 --> 00:07:13,843
When I grow up, I'm
gonna run a massive label.

109
00:07:15,136 --> 00:07:16,512
Do you have plans?

110
00:07:18,139 --> 00:07:19,140
No.

111
00:07:19,849 --> 00:07:21,433
He's a little nervous.

112
00:07:21,517 --> 00:07:23,217
Relax. He's walking in with Chloe.

113
00:07:23,936 --> 00:07:25,792
It's like walking in
with the golden ticket.

114
00:07:25,876 --> 00:07:26,522
[CHUCKLES]

115
00:07:26,606 --> 00:07:28,756
CHLOE: What kind of
music do you listen to?

116
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:32,779
Don't tell me. Bowie.

117
00:07:37,701 --> 00:07:42,455
<i>An autopsy is still being conducted
to ascertain the exact cause of death,</i>

118
00:07:42,539 --> 00:07:46,543
<i>but at this point, we can confirm
that the victim suffered a broken pelvis</i>

119
00:07:47,836 --> 00:07:50,172
<i>and a fracture at the base of the skull.</i>

120
00:08:07,523 --> 00:08:09,984
Come on, guys.
Would you put the guns down?

121
00:08:10,193 --> 00:08:13,321
Come on, Josh. You've got to
get your jacket zipped. Let's go.

122
00:08:14,906 --> 00:08:16,241
[CELESTE SIGHS]

123
00:08:17,408 --> 00:08:19,202
Perry, help me out here.

124
00:08:20,328 --> 00:08:22,628
What did we say about
shooting Mom before noon?

125
00:08:24,207 --> 00:08:26,417
-Guys. Really?
-Put the guns down. We have to go.

126
00:08:26,501 --> 00:08:28,336
I am not kidding, really.

127
00:08:29,546 --> 00:08:30,547
[IMITATING GUN]

128
00:08:30,713 --> 00:08:31,756
[GIGGLES]

129
00:08:36,886 --> 00:08:38,636
-First one to the car gets $1.
-Me!

130
00:08:42,268 --> 00:08:44,019
See? Just takes money.

131
00:08:46,021 --> 00:08:47,565
You are so bad.

132
00:08:48,566 --> 00:08:50,568
You love it when I'm bad.

133
00:08:51,569 --> 00:08:54,196
-So bad.
-You are. So bad.

134
00:08:54,280 --> 00:08:55,906
We are so bad.

135
00:08:56,407 --> 00:08:59,785
There should be like a five-year limit
on how long couples get to be gooey.

136
00:08:59,869 --> 00:09:01,704
He's a lot younger than her.

137
00:09:03,789 --> 00:09:06,083
-I don't wanna go.
-Do you really have to?

138
00:09:07,084 --> 00:09:08,586
Just two days.

139
00:09:09,628 --> 00:09:12,299
She must be pretty, you know…

140
00:09:12,966 --> 00:09:14,092
In the bedroom.

141
00:09:14,593 --> 00:09:15,969
Come on.

142
00:09:24,769 --> 00:09:25,812
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

143
00:09:25,979 --> 00:09:28,314
-Thank you. Great. See you then.
-It's so pretty.

144
00:09:28,398 --> 00:09:30,191
-I know, right? Isn't it gorgeous?
-Yeah.

145
00:09:30,275 --> 00:09:31,734
-Madeline, hello.
-Can me and Ziggy go play?

146
00:09:31,818 --> 00:09:32,902
Yes, of course. You guys go play.

147
00:09:32,986 --> 00:09:34,862
-Hi.
-How are you? Pregnant again?

148
00:09:34,946 --> 00:09:36,405
Of course, when am I not?

149
00:09:36,489 --> 00:09:38,074
-You look fantastic.
-Thank you.

150
00:09:38,158 --> 00:09:39,326
Did you…

151
00:09:39,784 --> 00:09:41,494
No, but you're sweet to think I did.

152
00:09:41,578 --> 00:09:43,455
-Well, you look fabulous.
-Thank you.

153
00:09:43,581 --> 00:09:45,499
Hi, Jackie. Good to see you.

154
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:48,544
Okay, Gabby is such a gossip.
We don't like her.

155
00:09:48,628 --> 00:09:50,212
Hey, Maddie, have you seen Justin at all?

156
00:09:50,296 --> 00:09:52,381
I think he whooshed past here.

157
00:09:52,465 --> 00:09:54,424
Are we doing the wine tasting
next week at your house?

158
00:09:54,508 --> 00:09:55,717
Yes, I'll send you an email.

159
00:09:55,801 --> 00:09:58,720
-I don't know where Ziggy went.
-He's with Chloe. He's fine.

160
00:09:58,804 --> 00:10:01,932
-Renata. Hi. Hi.
-Hi, Madeline, so good to see you.

161
00:10:02,016 --> 00:10:03,559
-You look adorable.
-Thank you so much.

162
00:10:03,643 --> 00:10:05,435
This is Jane Chapman. She's new here.

163
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:07,355
-Hi.
-Welcome. Renata Klein.

164
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,023
-Thank you.
-This is Amabella.

165
00:10:09,148 --> 00:10:11,775
-Hi.
-Hi. That's a beautiful dress.

166
00:10:11,859 --> 00:10:13,777
-How was your summer?
-It was wonderful.

167
00:10:13,861 --> 00:10:15,405
Very busy with the kids and camp.

168
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:17,366
-Just flew by.
-Same.

169
00:10:17,491 --> 00:10:18,616
How was yours, yeah?

170
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:20,869
Well, joined the board at PayPal.

171
00:10:20,994 --> 00:10:24,164
What was I thinking?
Adding one more thing to my life?

172
00:10:24,289 --> 00:10:25,874
-[CELL PHONE RINGING]
-But, you know… Oh, hold on.

173
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:27,041
These are my <i>Hamilton</i> tix.

174
00:10:27,125 --> 00:10:28,751
-Okay.
-I've seen it four times. Yes.

175
00:10:28,835 --> 00:10:30,962
I'll see you in there.
Here, come meet my best friend.

176
00:10:31,046 --> 00:10:32,297
Celeste!

177
00:10:32,881 --> 00:10:34,800
-Madeline.
-When did you get to town?

178
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:37,468
-Late last night.
-You didn't call me.

179
00:10:37,552 --> 00:10:40,180
-No, I'm sorry…
-And how did you get more beautiful?

180
00:10:41,181 --> 00:10:43,081
Oh. Baby, look, Madeline's over there.

181
00:10:45,352 --> 00:10:47,313
Yeah, we'll exchange numbers.

182
00:10:47,397 --> 00:10:49,440
-You're wearing the dress I bought you.
-I know.

183
00:10:49,524 --> 00:10:53,236
My new dress, my new shoes,
my new friend, Jane Chapman.

184
00:10:53,361 --> 00:10:54,987
-Hi, I'm Celeste.
-Hi.

185
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:57,406
She came to my rescue when I
was trying to save young lives.

186
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:59,575
It's a whole story.
I'm going to kill Abigail.

187
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:02,494
That's her son Ziggy right there,
playing with Chloe and the boys.

188
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:04,747
Can you believe that
they're in first grade?

189
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:06,498
I know. Take a lot of pictures.

190
00:11:06,582 --> 00:11:07,917
Hi, Maddie.

191
00:11:08,251 --> 00:11:10,545
-Come on, boys. Come on.
-Nathan, hi. Bonnie.

192
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,296
-And this is Jane.
-Hi.

193
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,549
This is Bonnie, Nathan, Skye.

194
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:18,052
-I love this.
-Thank you, I made it in Peru.

195
00:11:18,136 --> 00:11:19,805
Of course you did.

196
00:11:20,306 --> 00:11:23,391
You know, we were saying we should get
Skye and Chloe together for a playdate.

197
00:11:23,475 --> 00:11:26,603
I mean, they're half sisters, and
they pretty much never see each other.

198
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:27,729
It's ridiculous.

199
00:11:27,813 --> 00:11:29,815
Are they? Am I missing the math?

200
00:11:30,399 --> 00:11:31,983
HARPER: <i>We were all concerned
about Bonnie and Madeline</i>

201
00:11:32,067 --> 00:11:33,735
having their girls in
first grade together.

202
00:11:33,819 --> 00:11:36,238
You know, what that would
do to the classroom dynamic?

203
00:11:36,322 --> 00:11:38,188
And Abby is Chloe's
half sister, so we just…

204
00:11:38,272 --> 00:11:39,105
Right.

205
00:11:40,326 --> 00:11:41,952
-Thought…
-Of course. Just have Nathan call me.

206
00:11:42,036 --> 00:11:45,586
Yes, they have a common sister.
Can I have a word with you for a second?

207
00:11:45,748 --> 00:11:47,166
Um. Yes. Just one.

208
00:11:47,416 --> 00:11:48,750
-I just wanted to…
-What?

209
00:11:48,834 --> 00:11:51,504
I just wanted to ask you if you were
okay with swapping the weekends,

210
00:11:51,588 --> 00:11:52,838
if Abby can come with us this Friday?

211
00:11:52,922 --> 00:11:54,646
We're going up to Bonnie's mom's house in

212
00:11:54,730 --> 00:11:56,759
Camarillo, and Abby
doesn't want to miss it.

213
00:11:56,843 --> 00:11:59,593
She and Bonnie's mom actually
have a special connection.

214
00:12:01,181 --> 00:12:02,932
-Of course.
-Are you sure?

215
00:12:03,058 --> 00:12:04,267
Do I not look sure?

216
00:12:04,684 --> 00:12:06,769
Jane, we should go
because it gets very busy.

217
00:12:06,853 --> 00:12:07,853
Yeah, yeah.

218
00:12:07,937 --> 00:12:09,188
-Chloe!
-Nice meeting you.

219
00:12:09,272 --> 00:12:10,439
-Nice to meet you, too.
-Ziggy, come on.

220
00:12:10,523 --> 00:12:11,858
Come on, Zig.

221
00:12:13,026 --> 00:12:14,026
Come on.

222
00:12:14,110 --> 00:12:16,362
<i>We're looking at all angles.
Nobody has been ruled out.</i>

223
00:12:16,446 --> 00:12:19,866
So we're like seriously
using the word "murder"?

224
00:12:26,957 --> 00:12:28,607
MADELINE: I actually like Nathan.

225
00:12:28,793 --> 00:12:30,544
Okay, I wouldn't go all the way to "like,"

226
00:12:30,628 --> 00:12:33,578
but I accept and acknowledge
that he's a decent human being.

227
00:12:33,798 --> 00:12:36,383
I was just legitimately
surprised to see him at orientation

228
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:39,303
because it's not like he was
ever there for Abigail's first day.

229
00:12:39,387 --> 00:12:43,057
-And Bonnie is his new wife?
-Yeah, she's the very pretty one.

230
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:47,978
In fact, she's so pretty and
free spirited and Bohemian

231
00:12:48,062 --> 00:12:50,731
and all loving that
sometimes I just want to…

232
00:12:51,065 --> 00:12:52,566
Punch her in the face?

233
00:12:53,276 --> 00:12:54,319
Hey.

234
00:12:54,736 --> 00:12:56,655
You're gonna love this girl.

235
00:12:57,739 --> 00:12:59,189
Oh. Good, they saved my spot.

236
00:12:59,991 --> 00:13:01,410
-Hello, Tom.
-TOM: Madeline.

237
00:13:01,910 --> 00:13:03,161
What's happened to you?

238
00:13:03,412 --> 00:13:05,997
I've gravely injured myself.
I've twisted my ankle.

239
00:13:06,123 --> 00:13:07,624
Come meet my new friend, Jane.

240
