723
00:38:54,969 --> 00:38:57,596
MAX: The last time we
went, there was no leeches.

724
00:38:57,888 --> 00:39:01,338
PERRY: No, of course not 'cause I
was there, and they're scared of me.

725
00:39:01,726 --> 00:39:03,268
What, you didn't notice?

726
00:39:03,352 --> 00:39:06,252
Every time we go down there,
I just, like, scare them away.

727
00:39:06,439 --> 00:39:07,606
JOSH: How?

728
00:39:07,690 --> 00:39:10,861
PERRY: With my…
[BURPS] Burping superpower.

729
00:39:11,486 --> 00:39:12,571
[BOYS GIGGLING]

730
00:39:14,489 --> 00:39:16,839
PERRY: Do you want to know a secret?
JOSH: What?

731
00:39:17,242 --> 00:39:21,413
My superpower, I actually get it from Mom.

732
00:39:21,955 --> 00:39:24,166
-BOY: No.
-PERRY: You don't believe me?

733
00:39:24,666 --> 00:39:27,166
What did we have for
dinner tonight with the steak?

734
00:39:29,463 --> 00:39:32,591
-BOY: Mom's spinach salad?
-PERRY: Mom's spinach salad.

735
00:39:33,175 --> 00:39:34,425
[PERRY IMITATING BURPING]

736
00:39:34,801 --> 00:39:35,844
[BOYS LAUGHING]

737
00:39:36,678 --> 00:39:38,305
PERRY: Top secret, okay?

738
00:39:39,056 --> 00:39:40,506
[CONTINUES IMITATING BURPING]

739
00:39:41,851 --> 00:39:45,396
"G is for George, smothered under a rug.

740
00:39:46,147 --> 00:39:49,484
"H is for Hector, done in by a thug."

741
00:39:53,112 --> 00:39:55,323
-[GASPS]
-[PERRY CHUCKLES]

742
00:39:55,573 --> 00:39:58,284
-You startled me.
-I'm sorry.

743
00:40:01,454 --> 00:40:03,247
-These are great.
-Mm-hmm…

744
00:40:03,539 --> 00:40:04,582
Hmm.

745
00:40:07,835 --> 00:40:11,185
The boys mentioned something
about a little girl getting hurt today.

746
00:40:11,380 --> 00:40:12,423
Mm.

747
00:40:13,217 --> 00:40:15,135
Renata Klein's daughter.

748
00:40:15,219 --> 00:40:17,971
She wasn't really injured. She was just…

749
00:40:19,014 --> 00:40:22,434
Oh, look at this. Could they be cuter?

750
00:40:23,185 --> 00:40:24,978
PERRY: Oh.
I actually think this is my favorite.

751
00:40:25,062 --> 00:40:27,188
-I love your finger there.
-Stop.

752
00:40:27,272 --> 00:40:28,523
-Post it.
-All right.

753
00:40:28,607 --> 00:40:30,067
People are gonna love it.

754
00:40:30,275 --> 00:40:31,318
[CELESTE LAUGHS]

755
00:40:31,735 --> 00:40:33,403
Well, so what happened?

756
00:40:33,487 --> 00:40:34,779
With that girl.

757
00:40:34,863 --> 00:40:36,490
A boy tried to choke her.

758
00:40:38,408 --> 00:40:39,618
Are you serious?

759
00:40:39,827 --> 00:40:40,910
[SIGHS]

760
00:40:40,994 --> 00:40:43,121
Well, no one witnessed it,

761
00:40:43,205 --> 00:40:46,205
but she was pretty distraught,
and she had marks on her neck.

762
00:40:46,292 --> 00:40:47,627
Which boy?

763
00:40:49,087 --> 00:40:52,215
Um, this new boy, Ziggy.

764
00:40:52,757 --> 00:40:55,468
I mean, he seemed really sweet,

765
00:40:55,552 --> 00:40:59,972
and I met his mom, and
she couldn't be nicer, so…

766
00:41:00,056 --> 00:41:01,224
Yeah.

767
00:41:02,392 --> 00:41:06,242
Well, to be safe, we should tell Josh
and Max to keep their distance from him.

768
00:41:06,604 --> 00:41:09,106
-I don't think that's gonna be necessary.
-Honey.

769
00:41:09,190 --> 00:41:11,817
-If the kid is violent, we don't…
-No, he's not violent.

770
00:41:11,901 --> 00:41:13,851
Well, how do you know he's not violent?

771
00:41:14,154 --> 00:41:15,865
What, because he seemed sweet?

772
00:41:18,576 --> 00:41:22,163
-First off, he could be innocent.
-Or he could be guilty.

773
00:41:23,414 --> 00:41:26,124
We don't want the boys to be
getting mixed up with the wrong crowd.

774
00:41:26,208 --> 00:41:28,608
-They're six.
-They're not to associate with him.

775
00:41:34,008 --> 00:41:35,968
You're being ridiculous.

776
00:41:37,219 --> 00:41:38,345
[CELESTE SIGHS]

777
00:41:38,512 --> 00:41:39,596
[CELESTE YELPS]

778
00:41:39,680 --> 00:41:42,849
-The boys will stay away from that kid.
-Take your hand off me.

779
00:41:42,933 --> 00:41:46,283
If I can't be here to look out for
them, I need to know that you do.

780
00:41:47,104 --> 00:41:50,108
I asked you to remove your fucking hand.

781
00:41:55,447 --> 00:41:56,781
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

782
00:41:58,408 --> 00:41:59,993
[PLAYING PIANO]

783
00:42:03,288 --> 00:42:05,538
ABIGAIL: Is that a song
from your puppet show?

784
00:42:06,833 --> 00:42:09,836
Yes, but it's really more
than just a puppet show.

785
00:42:10,670 --> 00:42:11,712
[RESUMES PLAYING]

786
00:42:11,796 --> 00:42:13,714
[SOFTLY] <i>♪ Four years of college ♪</i>

787
00:42:13,798 --> 00:42:16,676
<i>♪ And plenty of knowledge ♪</i>

788
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:20,932
<i>♪ Have earned me this useless degree ♪</i>

789
00:42:22,516 --> 00:42:24,266
The play means a lot to you, right?

790
00:42:27,647 --> 00:42:30,608
I'll tell Bonnie to start a new petition

791
00:42:31,192 --> 00:42:32,485
in favor.

792
00:42:35,363 --> 00:42:37,031
Mom, are you okay?

793
00:42:37,615 --> 00:42:39,765
You're not like dying
or anything, are you?

794
00:42:40,826 --> 00:42:42,787
No, I'm not dying.

795
00:42:43,537 --> 00:42:45,137
What would make you ask me that?

796
00:42:45,331 --> 00:42:47,333
You seem a little wobbly.

797
00:42:47,875 --> 00:42:49,751
Are you having one of
your massive periods?

798
00:42:49,835 --> 00:42:51,171
No.

799
00:42:52,381 --> 00:42:53,757
No.

800
00:42:55,926 --> 00:43:00,472
What people don't tell you
is that you lose your children.

801
00:43:03,100 --> 00:43:06,019
As beautiful and wonderful as you are now,

802
00:43:07,354 --> 00:43:10,607
the little girl whose curly
hair I used to detangle,

803
00:43:10,691 --> 00:43:14,277
the one who had bad dreams
and would crawl into my bed,

804
00:43:14,361 --> 00:43:15,570
she's gone.

805
00:43:18,573 --> 00:43:19,616
Yeah.

806
00:43:19,783 --> 00:43:21,952
And I guess that's why
I'm feeling a little bit…

807
00:43:22,036 --> 00:43:25,957
Compounded by the fact that
your little sister's going to first grade.

808
00:43:28,084 --> 00:43:29,877
I'm losing my babies,

809
00:43:30,378 --> 00:43:34,382
which has been clinically
compared to a massive period, I think.

810
00:43:38,553 --> 00:43:40,555
I'll always be your baby.

811
00:43:42,056 --> 00:43:44,475
Bonnie's like a friend, you know?

812
00:43:44,726 --> 00:43:46,769
Maybe even a best friend sometimes.

813
00:43:47,645 --> 00:43:50,565
But I'm your daughter,
and you're my mother.

814
00:43:53,986 --> 00:43:56,405
Mom, don't cry.

815
00:43:57,948 --> 00:44:00,617
-Don't do that, okay?
-I'm sorry.

816
00:44:00,951 --> 00:44:01,994
[ABIGAIL CHUCKLES]

817
00:44:02,244 --> 00:44:03,579
I'm sorry. [SNIFFLES]

818
00:44:07,624 --> 00:44:10,711
Your hair, though, get it
out of your beautiful face.

819
00:44:12,796 --> 00:44:14,923
I can still call you babycakes, can't I?

820
00:44:16,258 --> 00:44:18,218
-Not in public.
-Okay.

821
00:44:18,510 --> 00:44:19,886
-[BOTH CHUCKLING]
-[DOOR OPENS]

822
00:44:19,970 --> 00:44:21,138
Oh, no.

823
00:44:21,638 --> 00:44:23,932
Not another one. You go back to bed.

824
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:30,273
[PLAYING PIANO]

825
00:44:39,366 --> 00:44:41,117
[HUMS ALONG SOFTLY]

826
00:44:43,953 --> 00:44:45,580
I love that song.

827
00:44:46,289 --> 00:44:47,889
Do you want to play it together?

828
00:44:48,833 --> 00:44:49,834
[INAUDIBLE]

829
00:44:58,969 --> 00:45:01,138
<i>We're treating the matter as a homicide.</i>

830
00:45:01,764 --> 00:45:04,141
<i>We have no suspects as of yet.</i>

831
00:45:31,002 --> 00:45:36,842
<i>I will say that we do believe we have
spoken to the person or persons involved.</i>

832
00:45:42,806 --> 00:45:43,974
Ziggy.

833
00:45:44,474 --> 00:45:45,600
Baby.

834
00:45:50,230 --> 00:45:51,647
What are we doing?

835
00:45:51,731 --> 00:45:53,431
You were sleepwalking again, baby.

836
00:46:05,580 --> 00:46:06,830
CELESTE: <i>Where are we
going to do the interview?</i>

837
00:46:06,914 --> 00:46:10,251
QUINLAN: <i>Right here.</i>
CELESTE: <i>I'll just put my purse down here.</i>

838
00:46:12,753 --> 00:46:15,653
NIPPAL: <i>The first thing I
said, it wasn't just the mothers.</i>

839
00:46:15,882 --> 00:46:17,758
GABRIELLE: <i>It was the dads, too.</i>

840
00:46:17,842 --> 00:46:19,176
STU: <i>The thing about fundraisers…</i>

841
00:46:19,260 --> 00:46:20,511
MELISSA: <i>They're vicious.</i>

842
00:46:20,595 --> 00:46:23,595
STU: <i>It's not the male grizzlies
